        def dfs(node, low=float('-inf'), high=float('inf')):
            if not node:
                return True
            if not (low < node.val < high):
                return False
            return dfs(node.left, low, node.val) and dfs(node.right, node.val, high)

        return dfs(root)
```

This works by carrying the valid value range down the tree. Each node must satisfy `low < node.val < high`; the left child narrows the upper bound to `node.val`, and the right child narrows the lower bound to `node.val`. Time: `O(n)`, space: `O(h)`.

