564.answer:
A priority queue needs two fast operations: add an item and remove the smallest (or largest) priority item. A heap supports this efficiently because it is a **complete binary tree** that maintains a **heap property**.

For a **min-heap**:
- Every parent node is `<=` its children.
- So the smallest item is always at the root.

Why this works for a priority queue:
- **insert**: put the new item at the end to keep the tree complete, then **bubble up** until the heap property is restored.
- **extractMin**: remove the root, move the last item to the root, then **bubble down** until the heap property is restored.
- Both operations take **O(log n)** time because the tree height is logarithmic.
- Getting the minimum is **O(1)** because it is always at the root.

Here is a simple JavaScript min-heap class:

```js
class MinHeap {
  constructor() {
    this.heap = [];
  }

  insert(value) {
    this.heap.push(value);
    this.bubbleUp(this.heap.length - 1);
  }

  extractMin() {
    if (this.heap.length === 0) return undefined;
    if (this.heap.length === 1) return this.heap.pop();

    const min = this.heap[0];
    this.heap[0] = this.heap.pop();
    this.bubbleDown(0);
    return min;
  }

  bubbleUp(index) {
    while (index > 0) {
      const parentIndex = Math.floor((index - 1) / 2);
      if (this.heap[parentIndex] <= this.heap[index]) break;

      [this.heap[parentIndex], this.heap[index]] = [
        this.heap[index],
        this.heap[parentIndex],
      ];

      index = parentIndex;
    }
  }

  bubbleDown(index) {
    const length = this.heap.length;

    while (true) {
      let smallest = index;
      const left = index * 2 + 1;
      const right = index * 2 + 2;

      if (left < length && this.heap[left] < this.heap[smallest]) {
        smallest = left;
      }

      if (right < length && this.heap[right] < this.heap[smallest]) {
        smallest = right;
      }

      if (smallest === index) break;

      [this.heap[index], this.heap[smallest]] = [
        this.heap[smallest],
        this.heap[index],
      ];

      index = smallest;
    }
  }
}

// Example
const h = new MinHeap();
h.insert(5);
h.insert(2);
h.insert(8);
h.insert(1);

console.log(h.extractMin()); // 1
console.log(h.extractMin()); // 2
```

