The adapter pattern lets incompatible interfaces work together by wrapping one object with another interface your code expects.

- **Intent:** convert one interface into another without changing the original class.
- **When to use it:** when integrating legacy code, third-party SDKs, or old APIs into a newer app design.
- **How it works:**
  - **Target**: the interface your app wants
  - **Adaptee**: the existing incompatible service
  - **Adapter**: translates calls/data between them

In your case:
- the app wants a **JSON-based interface**
- the legacy system returns **XML**
- the adapter will call the XML service, parse the XML, and return JSON

## TypeScript example

```ts
// Target interface: what the modern app expects
interface UserService {
  getUser(id: string): Promise<{ id: string; name: string; email: string }>;
}

// Adaptee: legacy XML service with an incompatible interface
class LegacyXmlUserService {
  async fetchUserXml(userId: string): Promise<string> {
    // Simulated legacy XML response
    return `
      <user>
        <id>${userId}</id>
        <name>Jane Doe</name>
        <email>jane@example.com</email>
      </user>
    `.trim();
  }
}

// Adapter: converts XML output into the JSON shape expected by the app
class XmlToJsonUserServiceAdapter implements UserService {
  constructor(private legacyService: LegacyXmlUserService) {}

  async getUser(id: string): Promise<{ id: string; name: string; email: string }> {
    const xml = await this.legacyService.fetchUserXml(id);
    return this.parseUserXml(xml);
  }

  private parseUserXml(xml: string): { id: string; name: string; email: string } {
    const getTagValue = (tag: string): string => {
      const match = xml.match(new RegExp(`<${tag}>(.*?)</${tag}>`));
      if (!match) {
        throw new Error(`Missing <${tag}> in XML response`);
      }
      return match[1];
    };

    return {
      id: getTagValue("id"),
      name: getTagValue("name"),
      email: getTagValue("email"),
    };
  }
}

// Client code: uses the modern JSON interface only
async function main() {
  const legacyService = new LegacyXmlUserService();
